-- Bankia says bad loan ratio 13.1 pct after latest credit portfolio sales
-- 
-- Fri Oct 24, 2014 04:44AM EDT
-- None



MADRID, Oct 24 (Reuters) - The bad loan ratio of Spain's nationalised lender Bankia <BKIA.MC> was 13.1 percent after the sale of credit portfolios worth 880 million euros (1.11 billion US dollar) in October, Chief Financial Officer Leopoldo Alvear said on Friday.

